President Joe Biden had a phone call with Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy, where he emphasized that the United States and its allies will respond firmly if Russia further invades Ukraine. They discussed diplomatic efforts, including the upcoming Strategic Stability Dialogue, NATO-Russia Council, and the Organization for Security and Cooperation in Europe. Biden reiterated the US commitment to Ukraine's sovereignty and territorial integrity, while also expressing support for confidence-building measures and active diplomacy to de-escalate tensions in Donbas and implement the Minsk Agreements.